Path: This week in Nu #43
Content:
JosephTLyons worked on helping 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2004] organize our growing set of math functions
, made 
``cal``
's 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1996] first day configurable
, removed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1976] some async_stream
andrasio added a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1999] median command
, fixed a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1998] regression in skip-until
fdncred added support for 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1993] viewing text with bat
, added a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1975] roadmap
kubouch added a command to 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1992] skip every n rows
, cleaned up some 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/50] website docs
arashout fixed a bug in our 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1988] yaml support
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1982] math docs
, moved some math functions to 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1969] math subcommands
utam0k cleaned up some 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1986] unnecessary clones
jonathandturner 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1984] bumped Nu to 0.15.1
, finished 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1983] removing async_stream
Since I forgot to mention last week: we now have an initial RFC process for large changes: https://github.com/nushell/rfcs
